# ğŸ”¥ How to Run Locally (MOST IMPORTANT)

FitScore AI backend **cannot be deployed to Deno Deploy** because Zypher requires a writable filesystem.
So you will run backend locally.

## 1ï¸âƒ£ Clone repo

```bash
git clone https://github.com/navyasharon/fitscore-ai.git
cd fitscore-ai
```

---

## 2ï¸âƒ£ Backend Setup

```bash
cd backend
```

Create your `.env` manually:

```
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_key_here
```

Run backend:

```bash
deno task dev
```

Backend runs on:

```
http://localhost:8000
```

If you see:

```
ğŸŸ¢ FitScore AI backend startingâ€¦
Listening on http://localhost:8000/
```

Youâ€™re good.

---

## 3ï¸âƒ£ Frontend Setup

```bash
cd ../frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

Frontend runs on:

```
http://localhost:5173
```

The frontend **automatically targets**:

```
http://localhost:8000
```

so no config changes needed.

